summaries.short: Tom learns of his family's past, as well as the reasons his great-aunt gave him the chest of curios.
summaries.full: Tom starts digging deeper into the life of his grandfather William, who he suspects might have competed in the 1948 London 'Austerity Games,' a far cry from those of 2012. Tom visits his great-aunt Victoria's friend Mildred, who is able to shed some light on why Victoria left Tom the chest of family curios. Bea and Monk perform their first professional gig.

summaries.short: Tom learns the secret that separated two Chadwick brothers, and connects with his American kin.
summaries.full: Tom learns the secret that separated two Chadwick brothers, and connects with his American kin. Tom, Bea, Keith, Luba and Monk drive up to the Derbyshire farm owned by their cousins from the North. Meanwhile, Pete has to perform a delicate procedure on an alpaca at the zoo. Pete's life-affirming mission at the zoo proves to be a no less sticky venture.

summaries.short: Tom heads to a regional theater in Sussex after learning that acting runs in his blood.
summaries.full: An unforeseen aspect of Tom's great-grandfather Harry's life leads Tom and Pete to England. They meet an old woman who remembers him from when she was a child. Their investigation takes them to a theater, where he and Pete learn more than they ever wanted to know about Harry's life. It also results in he and Pete entering a very unique competition.

Al has invited two other cousins--Rick, who also lives in California, and Dave, who's on a road trip from North Carolina--to a family barbecue.

summaries.short: Series Premiere. A recent inheritance triggers a young Englishman's yearning to discover his family roots.
summaries.full: Series Premiere. Unemployed and unattached, Tom Chadwick is surprised when he's bequeathed an old chest of curios by a great-aunt. An old photo in the box yields some very intriguing and revealing information about one of Tom's ancestors. Meanwhile, his old school friend Pete tries to get Tom's love life back on track by setting him up with a 'model pretty' date.

summaries.full: Tom's cousin Rick, an American Civil War enthusiast, helps Tom find out more about his great-great-grandfather. A car accident leads Tom to meet a beautiful aspiring writer, Ally Keele, and the attraction appears to be mutual. Tom gamely participates in a Civil War re-enactment. Mid-battle, he gets some news from England.
